    "en": "Developed in Mexico in the mid-1990s through controlled hybridization of Mexican Gray Wolves with domestic dogs, primarily German Shepherds and Alaskan Malamutes, to create a wolf-like companion breed that preserves cultural heritage while maintaining domestic dog temperament and trainability. Provisionally recognized by the FCI and the Federación Canófila Mexicana.",
    "zh": "20世纪90年代中期在墨西哥通过墨西哥灰狼与家犬（主要是德国牧羊犬和阿拉斯加雪橇犬）的受控杂交培育而成，旨在创造一种保留文化遗产、同时具备家犬性情和可训练性的狼形伴侣犬。获FCI和墨西哥犬业联合会临时认可。"
